    <AT-descriptions>
      <AT-description lang="en">The 'Mangroves of Bay of Bengal' is a regional ecosystem subgroup (level 4 unit of the IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology) that includes intertidal forest and shrublands of the marine ecoregions of Eastern India (Bay of Bengal province), Northern Bay of Bengal (Bay of Bengal province). The biota is characterised by 47 species of true mangroves and other key plant taxa that provide structure and resources for approx. 420 mangove-associated taxa. Mangroves in this subgroup have a mapped extent of at least ... km2 in ... countries and are predominantly ... and .... They are threatened by  conversion for urban and tourism development, agriculture and aquaculture, and by increases in frequency of tropical storms. </AT-description>
    </AT-descriptions>
    <AT-names>
      <AT-name lang="en">Mangroves of Bay of Bengal</AT-name>
      <AT-name lang="es">Bosques de Manglar de Bay of Bengal</AT-name>
    </AT-names>
    <Characteristic-biota>
      <Biota-Summaries>
        <Biota-Summary lang="en">The biota of 'Mangroves of Bay of Bengal' is characterised by the presence of 47 true mangrove and other key plant species. The range maps of Dolichandrone spathacea, Excoecaria agallocha, Kandelia candel, Aegialitis rotundifolia, Bruguiera sexangula, Rhizophora mucronata, Halodule wrightii, Rhizophora apiculata, Bruguiera cylindrica, Aegiceras corniculatum, Bruguiera gymnorhiza, Pemphis acidula, Brownlowia tersa, Ceriops decandra, Enhalus acoroides, Halodule pinifolia, Lumnitzera racemosa, Phoenix paludosa, Halophila beccarii, Sonneratia caseolaris, Sonneratia apetala, Avicennia officinalis, Heritiera fomes, Avicennia alba, Acrostichum aureum, Halodule uninervis, Heritiera littoralis, Avicennia marina, Rhizophora stylosa, Bruguiera parviflora, Aglaia cucullata, Ceriops tagal, Cynometra iripa, Scyphiphora hydrophylacea, Acanthus volubilis, Xylocarpus moluccensis, Xylocarpus granatum, Halophila ovalis overlap with most of the distribution of this unit. There are 420 species that have been associated with mangrove habitats in the Red List of Threatened Species database and that have natural history collection records or observations within the distribution of this unit (GBIF 2021). </Biota-Summary>
      </Biota-Summaries>
